          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>20 Dec 1850</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>My Dr <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I have received all your letters<lb/> with
                                        Prospectus &amp;c I have and am so afflicted by<lb/> the
                                        dangerous illness of my eldest Son that I have<lb/> not been
                                        able to attend to business with attention for<lb/> the past
                                        6 weeks 2 of which he has been between life<lb/> &amp;
                                        death. I hope that the change this week will be for<lb/> the
                                        better, but the disease is of so treacherous a nature<lb/>
                                        that I am never satisfied</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I will do all I can for you as soon as<lb/> my
                                        mind becomes more easy &amp; have the promise of<lb/> many
                                        subscriptions for the Bible</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philada</placeName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
